    "body": "I believe this due to the eyre hook because we currently \"panic\" on erroneous solc output.\r\ninstead, we should, as you suggested exit gracefully with std::process::exit(1)\r\n\r\nhere\r\nhttps://github.com/gakonst/foundry/blob/8c234f75937d7cd06f6101fc298fe36da369ca44/cli/src/forge.rs#L24\r\n\r\nor here\r\nhttps://github.com/gakonst/foundry/blob/8c234f75937d7cd06f6101fc298fe36da369ca44/cli/src/cmd/build.rs#L84-L97\r\n\r\nideally there should be two versions of `Build::run`, one that `std::process:exits` and one that we can reuse anywhere else which returns the error instead of exiting\r\n",
